## Backend surfaces (plain‑language API)
- `POST /api/web3/attest` { run_id, profile, api, inputs_hash, outputs_hash } → { tx, url }
  - Create a provenance receipt for a run.
- `POST /api/web3/ip/register` { dossier_id, contribution } → { contract, url }
  - Register an IP/royalty entry tied to a dossier and contribution split.
- `POST /api/web3/dataset/register` { dataset_hash, meta } → { tx, url }
  - Register a dataset manifest (hash‑only) with public metadata.
- `POST /api/web3/benchmark/register` { dataset_hash, metrics, profile } → { tx, url }
  - Register benchmark results for a dataset and profile.

Notes
- Backend implements chain adapters; FE only calls our API.
- All hashes computed server‑side; no raw data leaked.

## Roadmap (phased, with impact)
Phase 1 (4–6 weeks)
- Ship attestation flow for insights/efficacy/benchmarks (run provenance).
- Add “Verified on‑chain” badges and links in `ProvenanceBar`.
  Impact: immediate auditability; partner trust lift; faster diligence.

Phase 2 (6–12 weeks)
- IP/royalty contract registration from Dossier; contribution widget reads contract state.
- Dataset/benchmark registry + replication bounties.
  Impact: automated revenue sharing; growing public benchmark credibility.

Phase 3 (12+ weeks)
- Compute‑to‑Data integrations for partner cohorts.
- Token‑gated access to validated artifacts; marketplace for design assets.
  Impact: privacy‑preserving external validation; new monetization channels.

## Partner‑value metrics (investor‑focused)
- Provenance coverage: ≥90% of insights/efficacy/benchmark runs attested on‑chain by Q2.
- Time‑to‑audit: <30s to verify run provenance (hash match + profile flags) from UI.
- Royalty pipeline: ≥20 co‑inventor filings in year 1; platform contribution ≥30% on average; target royalty rate 2–5%.
- Cohort growth: ≥10 public datasets registered; ≥5 partner/private manifests; replication attestations ≥2 per benchmark.
- Benchmark marketplace: ≥50 registered benchmark entries; ≥30% replicated at least once; median AUROC/AUPRC lift documented per profile.
- Evidence velocity: ≥200 curated MoA‑targeted citations with reputation scores; 70% reused across dossiers.
- SaaS metrics: pilot ARR $250–500k in 6–9 months; gross margin ≥80%; payback <6 months.
- Attach rates: ≥60% of VUS users run WIWFM; ≥30% generate Dossier; ≥20% request cohort extraction.
- Time‑to‑value: <1 day to first attested run; <1 week to first cohort benchmark; <30 days to first co‑inventor claim.

## Risk & safeguards
- Privacy: PHI never on‑chain; only cryptographic digests and public metadata.
- Compliance: RUO maintained; on‑chain is provenance and licensing, not clinical claims.
- Quality: curation reputation + replication attestations mitigate low‑quality submissions.

## Quick examples (how, why, what)
- How do I verify a result?
  - Click the “Verified on‑chain” link in the Provenance bar → compare the run hash + profile; the explorer shows when it was recorded.
- Why should I register an IP/royalty contract?
  - It locks in fair, contribution‑based economics now, so there is no ambiguity if the asset succeeds later.
- What if I have a private cohort?
  - We post only a hash and public metadata. The data stays private; replication can run via Compute‑to‑Data later.

## Acceptance
- A run in VUS/Dossier shows an on‑chain attestation; link is visible; hash verifies.
- A benchmark registered from Data Lab appears in registry with metrics and profile.
- A Dossier can create an IP/royalty registration and display its contribution breakdown.



